-there are some commands used to monitor linux system.
1. df -h: Disk Filesystem 
--> shows disk usage of mounted filesystem.
-h means human readable (MB, GB)
-->checking the entire hard disk

du -sh : Disk usage
--> size of a specific directory/file.
--> checking the size od one folder/file

2. free -h :
--> shows RAM memory usage

3. lscpu:
--> showa CPU harware information

4. uptime :
--> shows
- current time
- how long the server has been running
- number of logged in users
- CPU load avg